# Installation #
################

There are two way of getting the source code.

    1. Mercurial:
        hg clone https://bitbucket.org/avinashjoshi/blob

    2. Download files and extract:
        http://bitbucket.org/avinashjoshi/blob

The easiest way to install blob is to download and install 'XAMPP' if you do not already have a web server setup. 

XAMPP is a very easy to install Apache Distribution for Linux, Solaris, Windows and Mac OS X.
The package includes the Apache web server, MySQL, PHP, Perl, a FTP server and phpMyAdmin.

XAMPP can be downloaded from:
http://www.apachefriends.org/en/xampp.html

Once you setup your database, and move the files to your document root directory, go to http://localhost/blob.
Read the next step to setup the database.

Admin User name = root
Admin password = toor

##################
# Database Setup #
##################

To set up the database, go to http://localhost/blob/setup.php then click on the 'Create / Reset Database' button.
This will create / reset the database for you with some data in.

Note:
    1. Make sure to delete/rename the setup.php file after installation! 
    2. The /hackable/users folder must be writable (777)

If you receive an error while trying to create your database, make sure your database credentials are correct within /config/config.inc.php

The variables are set to the following by default: 

$_BLOB[ 'db_database' ] = 'blob';
$_BLOB[ 'db_user' ] = 'root';
$_BLOB[ 'db_password' ] = 'toor';

